index.title: ROS 2 Robotics Education
index.description: Welcome to the ROS 2 Robotics Education module! This comprehensive guide will help you master ROS 2 fundamentals and apply them to control humanoid robots.

module-01-ros2/chapter-01/lesson-01-intr.title: Introduction to ROS 2 Concepts
module-01-ros2/chapter-01/lesson-01-intr.description: Learn the fundamental concepts of ROS 2 including nodes, topics, services, and actions

module-01-ros2/chapter-01/lesson-02-sett.title: Setting Up Your ROS 2 Environment
module-01-ros2/chapter-01/lesson-02-sett.description: Step-by-step guide to installing and configuring ROS 2 Humble Hawksbill on your system

module-01-ros2/chapter-01/lesson-03-basi.title: Basic Command Line Tools
module-01-ros2/chapter-01/lesson-03-basi.description: Master the essential ROS 2 command-line tools for node management, topic communication, and system inspection

module-01-ros2/chapter-02/lesson-01-unde.title: Understanding Nodes and Their Lifecycle
module-01-ros2/chapter-02/lesson-01-unde.description: Deep dive into ROS 2 nodes, their structure, lifecycle management, and best practices for node development

module-01-ros2/chapter-02/lesson-02-publ.title: Publishers and Subscribers Deep Dive
module-01-ros2/chapter-02/lesson-02-publ.description: Advanced concepts of ROS 2 publishers and subscribers including QoS policies, message types, and performance optimization

module-01-ros2/chapter-02/lesson-03-work.title: Working with Standard Messages
module-01-ros2/chapter-02/lesson-03-work.description: Explore ROS 2's standard message types including geometry_msgs, sensor_msgs, and other common message definitions

module-01-ros2/chapter-03/lesson-01-serv.title: Services - Request/Response Communication
module-01-ros2/chapter-03/lesson-01-serv.description: Learn how ROS 2 services enable request-response communication patterns for synchronous robotic operations.

module-01-ros2/chapter-03/lesson-02-acti.title: Actions - Goal-Based Communication
module-01-ros2/chapter-03/lesson-02-acti.description: Explore ROS 2 actions for long-running operations with feedback and status updates in robotic systems.

module-01-ros2/chapter-03/lesson-03-para.title: Parameters and Configuration Management
module-01-ros2/chapter-03/lesson-03-para.description: Master ROS 2 parameters for dynamic configuration of nodes and runtime system adjustments.

module-01-ros2/chapter-04/lesson-01-laun.title: Launch Files and Composable Nodes
module-01-ros2/chapter-04/lesson-01-laun.description: Learn how to create and use launch files to manage complex ROS 2 systems with multiple nodes and composable components.

module-01-ros2/chapter-04/lesson-02-buil.title: Building Production-Ready ROS 2 Systems
module-01-ros2/chapter-04/lesson-02-buil.description: Explore best practices and patterns for creating robust, maintainable ROS 2 systems suitable for real-world deployment.

module-01-ros2/chapter-04/lesson-03-simu.title: Simulation to Reality - Bridging the Gap
module-01-ros2/chapter-04/lesson-03-simu.description: Learn how to transition from simulation to real hardware, including hardware abstraction, sensor integration, and system validation techniques.

module-01-ros2/frontmatter-template.description: Brief description of what this lesson covers (under 160 characters)
